          "Questions, Answer Sequences",
          "[Sequence of Question-Anser pairs]",
          "DKT approaches use either RNNs or RNN-derived structures which makes thems vulnerable to deal with sparser datasets and/or longer sequences.",
          "The authors introduce a Transformer architecture which, at the time, was the state-of-the-art form of addressing sequential data.",
          "The model involves 2 forms of embeddings: A question embedding and an interaction embedding.\n\nThe authors also employ a normalization layer at the end of each layer: be it feed-forward or self-attention layer.",
